<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id4ccba8cb-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d" identifier="/us/usc/t34/s10512"><num value="10512">§ 10512.</num><heading> Applications</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">To request a grant under this subchapter, the chief executive officer of a State or unit of local government shall submit an application in such form as the Attorney General may require.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id4ccba8cc-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d">(<ref href="/us/pl/90/351/tI/s2402">Pub. L. 90–351, title I, § 2402</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/pl/103/322/tXXI/s210302/c/1/C">Pub. L. 103–322, title XXI, § 210302(c)(1)(C)</ref>, <date date="1994-09-13">Sept. 13, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/2066">108 Stat. 2066</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id4ccba8cd-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id4ccba8ce-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="id4ccba8cf-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section was formerly classified to <ref href="/us/usc/t42/s3796kk–1">section 3796kk–1 of Title 42</ref>, The Public Health and Welfare, prior to editorial reclassification and renumbering as this section.</p>
</note>
</notes>
